dct_description_sm: Printed with vegetation. Prepared by the U.S. Geological Survey for publication by the Defense Mapping Agency Hydrographic/Topographic Center. Variant title: Indiana 1:50,000. Variant title: Saint Paul, Indiana. Standard map series designation: DMA (Series) V751 Sheet 3862 I. Edition 1-DMA. "D.M.A. Series V851" "Transverse Mercator projection." Relief shown by contours and spot heights. Shows roads, railroads, boundaries, mines, man made structures, and natural features. "Contour interval 10 feet." "This map is red-light readable." Marginal maps: Elevation guide -- Adjoining sheets -- Boundaries. "This map is red-light readable." "Printed by DMAHTC 2-83." "Map information as of 1979." "DMA stock no. V751X38621."
Imprint: Reston, Virginia : Geological Survey, [1983]; Imprint: Washington, D.C. : Defense Mapping Agency, Hydrographic/Topographic Center, [1983]
Dimensions: 56 x 45 cm or smaller; Scale: 1:50,000
dct_creator_sm: United States. Defense Mapping Agency. Hydrographic/Topographic Center; Geological Survey (U.S.)
